UML:TaggedValue.value: A measure of the length of time for this time period such as hours, days, weeks, months, years.
The date, time, date time or other date time value which specifies the end of this period of time.
The date, time, date time or other date time value for the start of this period of time.
The name, expressed as text, of a person or department in the organization to whom incoming mail is marked with words such as 'for the attention of' or 'FAO' or 'ATTN' for this address.
The number, expressed as text, of a building or house on a street at this address.
The name, expressed as text, of the city, town or village of this address.
A name, expressed as text, of the country for this address.
The name, expressed as text, of a department within this address.
The first free form line, expressed as text, of an address.
A code specifying the postcode of the address.

The unique identifier, expressed as text, of a container commonly referred to as a box, in a post office or other postal service location, assigned to a person or organization, where postal items may be kept for this address.
A name, expressed as text, of a street or thoroughfare.
The text string of characters that make up the complete number for this communication.
The unique identifier of the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for this communication, such as a web or an email address.
A unique identification for this contract.
The code specifying the relationship between a declaration country and the place specified in this delivery terms, such as whether the place is located in the country where a declaration is made, ...
A code specifying a type of delivery for these delivery terms such as the INCOTERMS Terms of Delivery.
A textual description of the delivery terms.
A code specifying the risk responsibility for these delivery terms.
A quantity of goods or services billed for this delivery.
A date, time, date time or other date time value when the goods or services are or will be delivered for this delivery.
A date, time, date time or other date time value when the goods or services are or will be despatched for this delivery.
A quantity of goods or services that are or will be despatched for this delivery.
Shipping marks and numbers, expressed as text, put on the product or package units in this delivery.
The date on which the supply of goods or services was made or completed for tax purposes for this delivery.
A quantity of a unit for this delivery, such as a good or service unit.
A measure of a weight for this delivery.
A name or set of names, expressed as text, by which this person is known.
A textual expression of the title associated with a specific person, such as Doctor, Mr., Mrs., Ms..
A specific period of time such as the length of time between two known date/time points, from a start date onwards, or up to an end date.
The location at which a particular organization or person may be found or reached.
The exchange of thoughts, messages, or information, as by speech, signals, writing, or behaviour between persons and/or organizations.
An agreement between two or more parties, especially one that is written or spoken and enforceable by law.
The conditions agreed upon between the parties with regard to the delivery of goods and or services.
The action of distributing goods or services to their destination.
